text:
I travel Highway 45 to and from work.  I often saw African American boys playing basket ball in the left side yard of this church.  It didn't appear that they were disturbing anything.  This side yard was a good place for physical activity.
The church  now has a high wood fence between this area and a residence to the left of the church.  The fence has a no trespassing sign facing the home.
This a horrible display of the Christian spirit.  So sad, but very common in the South.
The fence should be removed.

resp.text: We hated to have to put the fence up, but the children were vandalizing our property. We also could not continue to accept the liability of the children playing in our parking lot and close to the road.  There had been many close calls in the Church yard but thankfully the accidents were averted.

name: Mary Hendershot
text:
Rivertown is a church that concentrates on reaching people who have been turned off or even turned away by some traditional churches.  They intentionally create an environment that is non-intimidating and not confusing to those who might be hesitant to attend church.
There is practical teaching delivered by live-streaming video that teaches how to relate and apply Biblical truths to life today so that you can have a better life.
The personal recognition of the benefits of deciding to become a follower of Christ on your own terms and in your own time replaces the pressure of an "altar call" to "get saved," terms and actions not easily understood by non-Christians.
There is no judgementalism or Bible-thumping, pulpit-pounding threat of hellfire. Just encouragement and good advice delivered with compassion and forgiveness, like Jesus did.
More emphasis on reaching and helping people with the truth of Christ, no emphasis on theological disputes.

resp.text: Mary, thank you for sharing your review of RCC.  We truly do exist to lead people into a growing relationship with Jesus Christ.

name: Charles Montgomery
text:
Tried the church for several weeks. What is disappointing is that there has yet to be an alternative call. In fact, last week the Pastor told people if they wanted to discover their purpose, meet him in the back... Then proceeded to take up the offering.

Now, the church live streams the service of another church on Sun morning. Why go to church to watch church on TV, when you can watch church on TV at home.

Is this what church has become? Very disappointed in what I have seen here and we will not be going back. There are too many churches in our area that have live, real life church services, and alter calls.

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback, Charles! I know it has been a while, but I wanted to share an update. We are currently in the process of launching a new expression of church on the Eastern Shore. BayLife Church will feature live, in-person teaching each Sunday. We officially launch Sunday, February 21. There are definitely other great churches in the area, too, if you prefer to worship somewhere that provides altar calls each week. We hope you have found the right church family, and you are always welcome here.

text: That particular facility is being forced to close its doors. Funding is sparse for such places. The residents won't have any place to go and need help. There aren't enough concerned people to help others that are lost. Some less fortunate people are considered as "throw-aways" , maybe not worth helping. As we sleep in our beds in moderate to luxurious comfort, there are some that struggle with their past's. Some are addicts, some are felons but most all need help to get back into society so they can be productive members again. All of them need a chance. But as facilities are forced to close for whatever reason, these people are cast back out onto the streets with little to nothing. Put yourself in their place, just for a minute. No one will ever read this. If there is even a single person, please pray for these people. They aren't garbage, they just need help. God bless you always.

text:
The pastor here preaches on scripture, not his own opinion.  He follows the Bible soundly and explains it in a way that is both easy to understand and in a deeply meaningful way that will make you sit back and reflect on the word of God.

The people here don't judge you.  They are open, friendly, and welcoming.  This is my favorite place in Tallassee to fellowship and learn about Christ!!!

name: Rachel Wingler
text: First Baptist Church is  a "Grace Place." It's a great place to learn from Biblical teaching, connect with great people of any age, and get involved in a community of people who understand that we are all recovering sinners with all sorts of backgrounds and all kinds of futures. Come as you are, however casual or formal you may be. With preschool, children's, youth, college, adult, and senior adult classes to choose from, you're sure to find a place to fit any stage of your life. The teaching available at every age and level is great, both in services and in small groups. It's grounded and understandable from preschool to senior adults. The worship style varies from southern gospel to hymns to current popular worship music. A normal service consists of singing, prayer, and teaching/studying of the Bible. There's a place for everyone here, and we'd love to have you! I found family, love, and grace here, and I hope you do, too.

name: Julie Reynolds
text:
Things you can expect at First Baptist:
1. There are two morning worship services and two Sunday school hours. You can go to Sunday school at 8:45 and then worship at 10 or do it the other way around.
2. Dress is casual, but people come dressed in all levels on the scale of informal to formal.
3. The music style is blended, leaning contemporary
4. Sunday School is very important to the overall experience at First Baptist. You get the family feeling in Sunday School and the feeling you are part of something bigger than yourself in the worship services. Adults will have more than one class to choose from; so, people try several classes until they find the one that fits them.

name: Jim Bearrentine
text: My wife and I were looking for a Bible based church where our whole family could grow.  After moving to the area we visited First Baptist.  The preschool is wonderful. There are activities for young children and teens, and there are many adult classes to choose from.  The pastor provides excellent Biblical guidance during the worship service. This energizes us and motivates us throughout the week. The Sunday School class provides opportunities to discuss real-life situations through a Christian perspective.  Most importantly, we feel that First Baptist is a place where our spiritual needs are met so that we can grow stronger in Christ, and from that we are challenged to go out and serve in the community and to meet the needs of others.

name: Brantley Chandler
text: First Baptist Church is very open and welcoming. There are people by the front door ready to shake your hand and give you a program when you walk in. The members enjoy meeting new people and helping them in any way they can. There are Sunday School classes for every age group and the classes are small making it easier to get to know new people and have a more personal relationship. First Baptist Tallassee is a very family friendly environment at the church there is a preschool wing for bed babies through 5, a children's wing for kindergarten through 6th grade, and a youth group for 7th through 12th. At First Baptist we have 6 main goals they are Christ centered worship, biblical instruction, prayer, world evangelization, nurturing fellowship, and caring acts. These goals are intended to grow Christians as individuals, as brothers and sisters in Christ, and to spread the gospel not only in Tallassee, Al but to the world.

name: Sharon Pride
text:
Nice church. Great daycare and preschool! My daughter attended preschool there from age 2 through K4. Tuition can be pricey & there can be a waiting list from time to time, but my husband & I believe it was worth it. The administration & staff are both knowledgeable & experienced. Admission to the preschool/daycare/after school care is limited. You either have to be buzzed in by staff or you have to have a security code to unlock the door. Children must be both signed in & out. Children are supervised at all times. Meals are nutritious & made on site by some truly wonderful ladies. Children are educated, cared for & loved by administrator & staff. We feel that our daughter's 3 years at FBCHPS has benefitted her educationally, socially & morally. She is 8 years old now & has been away from the preschool since she was 5 & what memories she has of her time there are precious to her. She misses it❤️

Although neither my husband nor I are members of FBCH, we have attended services there several times. We found the congregation & minister to be welcoming & warm. Congregants are kind & generous. There is ample parking for both the disabled & non. The church is wheelchair accessible & congregants are cheerful & helpful. This is a Community Oriented church. By that, I mean that the church & congregation are highly supportive of the Headland community & the schools of the City of Headland. I found the congregation & the staff of the preschool to be open, helpful & compassionate to the needs of members of the community once they were advised of needs. Very good people doing very good work for the Lord ⛪🏫🙏💕

resp.text: Dear Lorinda, As I read your review, I kept thinking that this did not sound at all like our church.  Then you mentioned reaching out to Pastor Kim and we have never had a pastor by that name at Passion Church, Montgomery, not even when we were formerly called Christian Life Church.  Since another church purchased our former property, my guess is that your experience occurred at our former building that was sold to them in January 2017.  That being the case and you have yet to find a church home, I invite you to visit Passion Church - Montgomery at 6825 Wares Ferry Rd. in Montgomery and ask an usher to introduce you to Pastor Norris or Cindy.  We believe in a miracle-working God who loves us and never gives up on us and here you will receive not just compassion, but an atmosphere where you can grow and mature in your faith and relationship with God through the redemptive power of Jesus, the work of the Holy Spirit and connecting with other believers in Small Groups.  We ALL need God and we ALL need each other, so I urge you "not to forsake assembling with other believers".  In any case, may God bless you and bring you to a place of wholeness & restoration and we would love the privilege of helping you get there.

name: Teresa Hill Berry
text: This is a huge Church for a disabled person not in a wheelchair there's a lot of walking. Will I go back no. Did I enjoy the service? The singing was way too loud the microphones could have been turn down halfway. A lot of screaming and yelling I don't know what they weresinging.  I saw about 40 members half of which were children. Five different people ask me the same question I explained I have COPD without the  machine. I repeatedly said please just let me sit down in the sanctuary. I guess I had on a large beautiful hat and they were looking for members. So that's what churches are doing now trying to reach you and size you up at the door wow. Maybe my big hat means I like my hat it doesn't mean I have a lot of money. That particular hat cost me $5 brand new  made by Essence  from the thrift store on Cooper Hill Road .It was a bad experience to go visit a church when each individual as I walked through I was asked where do you work where do you work where do you work then it was well where did you retire from where did you retire from 5 different people. Every time I looked around there was a different person it's cool with me to the sanctuary Give me a break after I greeted the pastor doing that very long walk which could have been much closer if they let you in the front door. For crying out loud. You would have thought that I was on a job interview I was just visiting on Easter Sunday. I had not gone to church on Easter Sunday since I was in my early 20s. At that time I was 64. The reason I stopped going on Easter Sunday is because all the preachers say the same thing you come to church on Easter Sunday to wear your new clothes. Well everything I had on was old real old nothing was new. That was another insult to injury from the long walk. Then I never ever heard any preacher from any denomination say this I Dare you to come back three Sundays in a row. I am 100% disabled I go to church when I'm Able. Not when the bishop DARES me. I tell you the truth this really is a New day. I think he should have been thankful for the people that came. No person is perfect no minister is perfect. I'm not a sensitive person however I could not wrap that around my head I dare you to come back three Sundays in a row who was he talking to his Members or his Visitors.These are things people are afraid to say. That should be a sign in the front yard of the church that says enter from the rear of the building I explained I was Disabled that was no secret when I looked at how far I had to walk from one ramp to another ramp down this long Hall to get to the sanctuary. Preachers preach about be careful of the tongue. That goes both ways. The Bishop voiced his opinion and I have voiced mine. Now I know why they want to know time you get there what church are you a member of or do you attend. Are they calling the church to get a reference on you this is ridiculous why.

name: Rachel Hilley
text:
When I was following Gods voice for a three day period, on the streets of Prattville, alone & growing weary. Thirsty, tired & hungry. God sustained me & when I was about to give up all together, instead God passed me along to this church, along my path & my burdens were given up to Jesus as soon as I walked into the door. Consumed with love & no judgment your beautiful ministry & church & new pastor & his administrative staff took me in your building as I walked inside and spoke with me, counseling me with great compassion & mercy. You fed me Mexican food from next door & gave me water to drink & even some soda. 🙏 you all went out of your way to help me even when you did not understand what was troubling me, or why I had chosen to leave home. You did not push me to answer you or make sense of it. But you allowed me to rest, coming miles down the road in a place unknown to me by city. In a walking boot that my recovering foot was in. Your pastor gave me great advice & even the administration’s licensed nurse checked out my foot, to make sure it was in tact & still in good health. You were patient with me. You all served the kingdom perfectly & I know when I was just about to give up Jesus led me a mile or more directly to you, & when I saw your building I knew in my heart that I would be okay & I had great peace. No one else would help me, or give me water to drink. Leaving behind three days prior a family members home after a great argument, leaving behind all my possessions, safety. And even my financial means & with no understanding why I would be doing what I was people everywhere looked at me with judgment as I walked up the roads of Prattville. In a walking boot alone I’m sure I looked odd & also not understanding I had chosen this path & yet I was far from homeless. There is and shouldn’t be any judgment upon the homeless or wandering any way though. I would say we all have fallen short and wandered for times in our lives, even if it was not on a strange and Public street.  But the truth is I have certainly been that homeless woman and many more types of people the world chooses to look down upon. But not our father in heaven, or his true disciples. Made perfect in Gods perfect will & love. Transformed by the renewing of our minds. & changed and transformed by Gods never failing or ending grace!  God assured me you all could be trusted and your pastor gently led me & made sure I was to make it back to my family.God will not forget your acts of kindness and even now he is providing superabundance and potent blessings and favors upon your church & all people involved with you evermore. Shalom family, I will never forget any of you & again thank you for your true acts of LOVE ❤️Christ calls us to live by and through.
I am reminded of these verses from Matthew 25:31-40

“When the Son of Man comes in his glory, and all the angels with him, he will sit on his throne in heavenly glory. All the nations will be gathered before him, and he will separate the people one from another as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats. He will put the sheep on his right and the goats on his left.

“Then the King will say to those on his right, ‘Come, you who are blessed by my Father; take your inheritance, the kingdom prepared for you since the creation of the world. For I was hungry and you gave me something to eat, I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink, "I was a stranger and you invited me in, I needed clothes and you clothed me, I was sick and you looked after me, I was in prison and you came to visit me.’

“Then the righteous will answer him, ‘Lord, when did we see you hungry and feed you, or thirsty and give you something to drink? When did we see you a stranger and invite you in, or needing clothes and clothe you? When did we see you sick or in prison and go to visit you?’

“The King will reply, ‘I tell you the truth, whatever you did for one of the least of these brothers of mine, you did for me.” (NIV)

Sincerely yours,
Rachel N. Hilley

text: When church names sounds more like a fancy restaurant or club (i.e. the Brook, the Rock, the Well, New Eden) it tells me that the church is more focused on appearing hip to modern Christians than being serious about the faith. When did pastors being reverent, godly, and sober get replaced with men/women that seek to be fashion and pop culture icons? These are sada times indeed.

resp.text: Kenzie, thank you for sharing your thoughts on church names. For us, we chose the name “New Eden Church” primarily based on the vision in Revelation 22:1-5. In that passage, we see the original garden of Eden made new by the work of Jesus. This garden where God and humanity were one is now recreated and populated by people from every nation, tribe, and tongue - all worshiping the slain Lamb with a unified voice. This is the vision that motivates us, and we are very serious about seeing that happen. And the good news is we know it will happen, because Jesus is going to accomplish His work. We just want to be a part and see foretastes of His final Kingdom in the here and now through and among this humble church. We’d love to have you visit sometime! If you have any questions, please email us at info@newedenchurch.org.

name: Tyrone Barton
text: Member for about 7 years. We love the Missional Community Group structure. To be blunt this is not a place to warm a seat. This is not a southern "country club" church. You need to be active in a group and participate in order to be recommended for membership. You can, however, start being active in a Missional Community Group right away. We are designed to do life together, to disciple. -- We have also been missionaries sent by Summit in our past work. -- You can expect: Expository preaching with occasional "one-offs". We collectively follow daily community bible reading and pray. Instead of inventing new projects or programs they encourage you to get involved locally and internationally with other ministries and organizations that are already established(think: serve day, manna house, downtown rescue mission, CRU...). Be the church, not the name or the building.

name: Deborah Suggs
text: Summit Crossing is an Acts 29 church whose mission is to encourage one another to know the Gospel, connect in Gospel relationships, and live out the Gospel in the world. The music is in a contemporary style but all songs are carefully chosen for their theological content as much as their sound. The sermons are heavy in Biblical exposition rather than being topic-driven. Children's ministry is active on Sunday mornings for babies up through 6th grade. Missional communities (MCs) are the small groups that meet during the week to study the Bible, discuss the sermon, and encourage one another in Gospel living. There are MCs for the student ministry as well (7th-12th grades). If all you want is a church that will make you happy and preach feel-good sermons, this isn't the place for you. But if you are serious about following Jesus and reaching others for Him, this is a good place to be.

name: Kenneth Hale
text: My complaint is not geared toward the Salvation Army but the security company it employs to run its shelters. I'm not alone in my experience with them. It's hit and miss when you call to reserve a bed at the Huntsville facility. I thought emergency shelters were for emergencies yet they expect you to plan tour emergency and call ahead and if you don't you are turned away regardless if there was no answer or if they have empty beds or not. The current guards have me waiting outside knowing I'm scheduled to have major surgery in the morning telling me that I did not register yet I spoke with the director here earlier this afternoon and register. Things like this happen often here they even turned a blind man away with spare beds. I'm currently gathering eye witness accounts of other episodes and sworn affidavits to present to the concerned party. I've talked with at least a dozen such people and hope to get more. I feel that a charitable organization as yourselves should be more understanding to the often I'll and mentally I'll. I look forward to speaking with someone from your organization concerning these matters. Yours Truly Kenneth Hale

name: Rachel Sullivan
text:
Movement Church is all about loving people so they can have a move fulfilling relationship with Jesus. So often life, and religion, tells us we are not good enough, we have failed, fallen short,  or won't amount to anything because we have made mistakes... Movement is here to set the record straight - using scripture. How refreshing!!

Is this the perfect church, filled with perfect pastors, and perfect people? Absolutely not. But it is filled with people whose heartbeat is to ensure the gospel reaches the ends of the earth!! The ministry here comes from the heart, and if you are open to a different kind of church experience, I assure you, the love will be felt deep in your soul.

We would love to see you on Sunday, stop by and give us a try ;)

Mostly all 5 stars is a sign of mindless devotion. Something is very wrong.  Likely greed and self contentedness is at play.  This was written a few days ago about this church by an acquaintance of mine -- someone who attended there but is now leaving:

[I hate feeling the need to post this. However Movement church in Madison, Al has spent the last 3 years priding themselves as being welcoming and forthcoming in the LGBT community. The pastors spoke at LGBT members weddings, baptized LGBT people, and allowed them to participate in various departments. As of this week, they met with LGBT members of the music department and asked them to step down because they choose to continue to sin and they can not hold roles of leadership in the church any longer. Not only that, but the letter that went out from the pastors made THEM seem like the victims in this. "We cried buckets of tears", "we fasted for days over this"... I have the full letter if anyone would like to read this. It crushes me that myself and so many others are hurting in our area over this.]

name: Jane Doe
text: I write this review anonymously because I am afraid of retaliation from the church family itself. The family of pastors at this church will make you feel like you finally belong somewhere. They will make you feel like family. They were pastors of a church in Eustis Florida called Family Bible church. They abandoned their congregation for fame from a new reality show, which completely tanked. Whatdoyaknow?  The amount of hurt and chaos associated with their decision to move destroyed the very faith that they helped build in many of their youth group regulars as well as their main adult congregation. I personally attended their youth group regularly. I practically lived at that church. When they moved and abandoned our congregation, I lost my faith. I now do not even know what to believe in anymore. It was almost as if our issues were too much for this family to combat anymore so they just gave up, packed their bags, and went on with their lives. I have witnessed the aftermath of the youth group kids that they left behind. The turmoil in their hearts and lives is astonishing. These were kids i considered family. These were kids that are now struggling because not only did their pastoral family leave, they completely cut ties and no longer talk to most of the kids that attended their church. They had no regard for the people who attended the church. Nor did they care what pastor they left their church with. It's hard to believe that such horrible, self centered people could create such a following in the bible belt of all places. You would think people from that area would be able to see and recognize false prophets and people who are only in the church game for the money. It's sickening. I'm just saying as a Speegle, Adgate, Windham family survivor that these people are not worth it. They don't actually care about you. They are in it for their own personal interests. There are plenty of churches in your area that have a pastoral staff that are in it for the right reasons and not just the money and popularity.  Their love for you is fake, the things they preach are false, and they will abandon you just like they abandoned us in Florida. "Preach for the money, You're a waste of a preacher." Fin.

text:
Our family moved to Huntsville in the summer of 2017 and we visited this church while looking for a home church.
While this church is not where we settled, I can honestly say it was the BEST sermon I heard in this area. I still listen to Pastor Blair’s expository preaching online and I love his commitment to the truth of God’s word and how he explains difficult passages with so much clarity. I find his teaching very thorough, challenging and humble.
The fact that he doesn’t use the KJV was a huge plus for me ( someone mentioned it as a negative) because I truly believe there are more accurate translations out there than the KJV.

( disclosure about why we settled on another church: our family is a family of 5 and we simply have different needs and personalities so another church in the area came in first place when we all voted. That being said, our impression was that Providence Baptist is also a wonderful, God-honoring church.)

name: Ric Crooks
text: Providence Baptist Church (PBC) is a traditional, God-centered Reformed Baptist church.  PBC aligns itself with the 1689 LBCF; and centers on making and training disciples in God's word, stirring one another up to love and good works, and actively supporting missions.  I equate their adult Sunday School classes to seminary-style classes, with different levels based upon your current understanding of various Biblical truths.  The children's and youth classes are focused on teaching Scripture in a God-centered way.  The Worship Service follows the regulative principle of worship (prayer, singing [from hymnals], reading Scripture, expository preaching, and administering the ordinances).  It is a wonderful place to worship God alongside His people!

name: Brandy Dowdey
text:
Church at the Crossing is a great place to worship and connect. One might expect to be guided through the parking lot by smiling faces and greeted at a “visitor tent” by other volunteers from the church.  Upon entering the foyer you will encounter more greeters and the aroma a coffee. It’s not just free, it is also good too!
First and second time visitors get a gift for visiting and these gifts are unlike any other! They are GREAT! The first one is something the whole family can enjoy together and the second, well it is individualized. I won’t ruin the surprise I case you plan to attend a few times.
Have kids? They have an excellent children’s ministry for ages 0-5th grade. There is a check-in process for children that allows parents to know their child is secure and can only be picked up by them as well as an electronic way to notify a parent if they were needed. The children’s ministry is interactive and has a high level of intensity. Your child will not get bored, and that’s for certain.
To say the worship is contemporary would not be doing it justice. It is much more than that, it is alive, engaging, and compelling. It’s hard not to at least sway back and forth. Worship at Church at the Crossing is an experience.
The messages are practical and applicable to every day Christian living.
There are two Sunday morning services times, 9:00 a.m. – 10:15 a.m. and 10:30 a.m. - 11:45 a.m. Having options allows for church to fit a normal flow for you and or your family. Hey, if you choose the second service you are out by noon, hopefully beating that lunch crowd!
Church at the Crossing doesn’t end with Sundays, they also offer Life Groups on a semester basis. This makes it easy to connect with people of similar interest or with others in similar phases in life.
Speaking of connecting, serving is a large part of this church. Not only do they make it easy to connect on a serving team but they also make serving fun!

The performance by the First Baptist Church Choir is completely amazing. I love to sing at church, but this was different. I found it so beautiful that I caught myself just wanting to listen and enjoy the peace it brought to me hear God being praised so amazingly and beautifully. The Sunday School classes that they offer here covers any preference that you can imagine from the children's classes all the way to the various adult classes as well. I was very, very grateful that the lessons covered by their classes teaches the same criteria to children, in their own understanding, as well as it teaches the adults. That is a togetherness unrivaled by my experiences up til now. Like I previously stated, at First Baptist Church everyone is on the same page so to speak. I love learning about God. This is a great place to gain more knowledge about "The Rock" in my life. This is a true home for building on and creating the perfect foundation.

name: David Moultry
text: Without fear of contradiction it’s a place you are certain to find God. A place where a moving of the spirit happens regularly. Bishop Sutton is the real deal! Granted there’s no good in any of us (thus said the word of God) however he’s truly a man of God that lives, eats and breathe the gospel of Christ. His vision has become the launching pad to hope, love, peace, the truth, and family life the way God intended it to be. Newlife has been nothing short of a blessing to me. The preaching, teaching and culture exemplifies the meaning “NEW LIFE”. If you’re looking for a church home search no longer, for this is the place! Come consumed with expectations and who knows what might happen. It’s a powerful ministry!

name: Tristan Hood
text:
I absolutely love this church! The preaching and teaching is the best I’ve experienced in the 30 years I’ve been attending church. The people are warm, inviting, thoughtful, funny, and full of the Holy Ghost. I’ve never gone and not experienced an excellent move of the Spirit.

I’ve worked with the people of New Life and they are top notch. The Praise and Worship is the best I’ve experienced and it’s largely because they put the emphasis on worship. The pastor consistently prays for the praise team during the worship service, the flow is phenomenal and they have the process down to an art. The exhortation is powerful and, again, the preaching is thought provoking and filling.

I’m proud to have experienced 7 years of my spiritual journey at New Life and count it an honor to call its people my friends.

name: Joyce Pugh
text:
I visit my sister Anne Posey who is a member if Sunview Baptist. I go to church with her and my nephew Keith Posey faithfully. The past 3 months ( March,April, and May ) I have gone to many churches in my past but I just knew God sent me here cause this is the one where I belong. He knew if any pastor and Sunday school teacher could reach me... It would Chris our senior Sunday school teacher and Pastor Brother Mark Boyd. I am going to share an experience that happened to me one Sunday. Chris was teaching class and as soon as he started talking he caught my full attention that day.... never in many years has that happened to me!! I mean my mind didn't even stray for a second!! Then we were in church for our daily service... boy... can Brother Mark touch a soul...cause that day he really drew me into his God.  We sang a song Lift Up The Cross... oh what a touching heart felt song. Again Brother Mark caught my attention and I wouldn't astray from him. at the end of the sermon as we stood for those to come forward i felt a coldness run through my body as I then felt like I was dizzy,  light headed of course I got scared and started praying dear Lord please make this feeling go away...well it didn't my heart started beating fast due to anxiety built up I was starting to turn to my sister and tell het how I was feeling and needed to step out. But, out of no where a warm sensation went up my stomach through my chest and out of nowhere this most beautiful sensation went through me and I felt such a peacefulness and contentment within me. It wasn't until we left to go for lunch afterwards that started crying cause that was an experience I have never had. I told my sister about it and she said the Lord Jesus came into my soul. Let me tell you something... I will never forget that beautiful moment. For I will take it to the gave with me. This is not a made up story it really happened to me. I  finally talked to Brother Mark about my experience and he was amazing in helping me understand the Holy Spirit touched my soul that Sunday.He took the time to sit down with me and even read some verses from the bible to help me understand. so now I am no longer frightened if what I experienced that wonderful,day.
Thank you Brother Mark and Chris
I can't wait to visit again to see all of you. My friends, my church, my Godly home. The people there make you feel welcomed and make you feel like you belong. And that's not fake either just love them all to pieces. I want to thank my sister for bringing and introducing me to her Christian family.
May God bless all and everyone of you.

name: Krissi Faith
text: Please like and follow our reviews. Wheelchair accessible. If you chose to visit for the sabbath Saturday service, arrive 15 minutes early. Seating is hard to come by once the service begins. Very unique style congregation of folks from all various backgrounds. Saturday main service begins promptly at 10:30am. There are several segments of their service which are performed by different members. There are several Jewish songs and dance followed by more modern worship songs in English. They also recite parts of the Torah. Everything is projected on the wall for new comers. After each meeting, everyone eats and socializes. It is was an extremely welcoming place full of culture and Hebraic biblical teachings. They also have a segment where they pray special blessings over the children. There even Hebrew classes taught here as well. Visiting the Messianic Worship Center felt foreign for its diversity yet familiar like home. Would definitely recommend this place

text:
A lovely and simple Place of Messianic Worship.
My husband and I visited and were both made to feel welcome. The atmosphere was both friendly & relaxing. The teaching was interactive & informative and the overall Judeo-Christian experience was refreshing.
On our particular day of visitation we weren't prepared to stay afterwards but it appears they continue fellowshipping with pot-luck style food and conversation which is always a nice touch of community.
We received a thoughtfully hand written  thank you card from the Pastor/Rabbi in the mail a few days after our visit, welcoming us back and stating their desire to be of service if ever needed. We hope to return again soon!

text: I attended The Rock Church last night and loved it. Mattie Montgomery preached and it was unreal. That was the third time I heard Mattie and last night was his best by far. That being said, we need to think the best in our brothers and sisters in Christ. Money is a tough thing to talk about in the church, but it is necessary. I would rather give money to this church than to some of the other places I've chosen to spend God's money. We need to leave the affairs of the church with God and refrain from passing judgment. I am sure that this place is not a cult and am happy to finance their efforts to improve the lives of others by bringing them to Christ. I look forward to attending their service again. The staff was amazing and I enjoyed meeting Pastor Caleb. And as always I will spend my time praying for my church leaders and will leave the judgment to God. Thanks for a great night.

text: They seem to love the Lord ,but they don't appear to want to embrace the ENTIRE Word (both Old and New Testaments) as God's Word. When I questioned them online about certain theological issues they don't do political issues.  Fair enough. It wasn't about politics, but I can't go to a church that cherry picks only certain scriptures because some of them don't line up with what's agreeable to them. I'm not saying that they don't love Jesus,  but the ENTIRE Word of God is for the body of Christ and must be received as such. To do otherwise is dangerous. I'll be praying for them.

name: Andy
text:
I walked into this church for the first time and was met with a great worship experience. I sang my guts out in worship and praise of Jesus and felt lucky to have the lead male singer sit behind me.

Little did I know that I wasn’t very lucky at all.

Just as Pastor Jimbo was teaching about the Great Commission (go into the world, meaning other countries as well), in a sermon about how we as Christians are call to create healthy environments for people to grow in Christ and to evangelize by creating fulfilling relationships....

This worship leader whispered to his girlfriend, pointing to me, saying “Is that a Mexican?” in a negative, hateful tone.

His girlfriend (Jessica?) then also pointed and whispered the same thing to her friend. “I think that’s a Mexican right there.”

I did not grow closer to God from that, nor was it a healthy environment, nor was that an example of bringing people closer to God through healthy and nurturing relationships.

And to think that this racism came from the lead worship singer, the person I was singing along with to revel in my faith and give glory to God.

As I looked around, I noticed that I was literally the only person in this small nondenominational community church who wasn’t completely white.

But I definitely felt like the most Christian and the most American.

Somebody reached out and as he heard my story he apologized to me, but then tried to make the excuse of “This is Birmingham in the Deep South, we’re not going to be perfect.”

Non-whites beware.

Racists are a tiny minority both in this city, in this state, and in this country — but when you find a community who accepts it as a normality... Just run.

That is not Christian, and it’s not where you should bring any friends you reach out to.

name: Heather R. Houston
text:
At Coastal Church, they love & accept everyone, no matter who you are or what your background is; they genuinely care & show unconditional love for ALL, the way Christ teaches.
It is a fun laid back setting but does not veer from biblical truths & teaching of the Word.  I love the message & practical teachings each week. I don't go out of obligation or guilt, but because I love it & the people that make up Coastal Church. It is like therapy for my soul & spirit.
I was raised in the South, grew up in the Bible Belt, & have gone to great churches my entire life, but This small church in Daphne, AL is really something special... they are the Real Deal, & that is hard to find even in churches.  I am grateful & feel blessed that God led me here.

name: Nancy Simpson
text: I love the teaching. The Pastor is very insightful on a lot of things. Do I agree on everything he says, no, but that's OK I can chew up the meat and spit out the bones. I like the community feel of the church. I like the fact that they help other organizations. I would like to see more praise and worship and alter  calls. I would like to see more lifting of hands and praising the Lord in song and dance and worship. Worship  brings in the presence of God every time. I'd like to see more praying  and laying on of hands for salvation and healing and deliverance and other things that the CHURCH  is so in desperate need of. A church is just building meant to bring Polin to hear the gospel, to get saved, for Christians to get rejuvenated and recharge, but We the children of the most high God are THE CHURCH!!!! The pastor is the Shepherd of the sheep as it says in God's word. He is accountable for that sheet. He is held at a much higher standard. I understand that people interpret the word of God differently but pastors are held in a much higher understanding position. Having said That, it's imperative that he is totally led by the Holy Spirit and what comes out of his mouth for he will be held accountable. And Whitney, the sheep, are the ones to go out and beget other sheep to bring into the fold. It's not all on the pastors shoulders. They have a Lotta home groups which is a good idea but just make sure that those home group leaders are born-again spirit filled men or women of God!

text:
I.V. Marsh and his wife, Bené Marsh, co-pastor Epic Church.  Epic is located in an upgraded, renovated movie theater.  Don't get this wrong -  you'd never even know it, except for this post.

Y'all come!   You're always welcome.

I.V. is like no other pastor.  He presents the wisdom of God's words with a warm invitation, in an easy-to-understand, often humorous, rarely experienced, not-to-be-forgotten, style.

In two years of attending Epic, each Sunday is a surprise.  Ya' know, like a box of chocolates - you never know what you're gonna get.  Feel free to bring your smart phone with your Bible app, your Bible, or not.

Come broken.  Come mended.  Come listen, and be healed.  Epic welcomes you, because you belong.  Uh, yeah, I mean ... y o u .

name: Memphis Seoul
text:
Today was my first time visiting this non-denominational Church and it would most likely be my last. The two great things that I loved about this Church was that me and my guest felt welcomed and that the pastor did preach about Jesus :) However, I thought that it was unnecessary to play secular 90's music for the first 15 minutes of worship at the altar instead of Praise and Worship. Is this church praising God or the things of this world?! Why couldn't we used those 15 minutes to do an altar call for the lost instead of singing secular songs?!!  I was really disappointed in my brothers and sisters for doing this. God should get ALL THE GLORY AND ALL THE PRAISE!!! Church is about Seeking the Lost, Teach the Found, Send the Disciples. I felt like God was just sitting there saying "Hey! Worship me! DON'T slap me in the face with this 90's crap at the altar!" I had to humble myself and the Holy Spirit said unto to me this is why the Church is not as strong as what it use to be because of the things in this world has become such a distraction."
However, this is a good stepping stone church for maybe junior high or high school kids and even those that are "babies" in Christ that recently accepted the Lord as their Savior." Since I have been a Christian for so many years, I really wasn't spiritually fed with the Word today as I would have when I listen to John Piper, Pastor Diego Mesa, Chris Wienand, and so forth... I felt like this pastor needed some more growth with the Lord and I don't recall seeing a Bible in his hand. It's one thing to have an Iphone, Ipad but it's another when you have the NKJV Bible, (the root!) in your hand. Again this is what makes us not look like the world. But I strongly stress an altar call and giving God extra time to worship, extra time in His word just to be close to Him gathered together in His name.
If Jesus wasn't preached today, Epic Church would just be a big, entertaining, social club.
For those that are mature in Christ, I strongly suggest another Church that you can get rooted, grounded and spiritually fed elsewhere. But for those that are young, kids, maybe early twenties this Church MAYBE for you. But, you HAVE TO grow.

Jennifer

text: Not once but twice, I had to deal with racism in this church. Also when I was dropping my kids off at the kids area I had this man walk up to me, look me up and down  and asked, “what do you do for a living, that you can look like that?” I laughed a little cause I thought he was joking, so I said, “what’s that?” Just to see if he would say it again. Without missing a beat he asked the same question again. Then I saw he was serious. I said I am a disabled vet. He looked me up and down, sucked his teeth, and turned around and just walked off. I guess that’s what I get for having long hair, in a church in Dothan. Needless to say, we didn’t go back! I have never been so insulted in a church.  Not only was it a insulting question about how I looked, it was a slap in the face to veterans who fought for this country, and got disabled in the process! So if your looking for racism and people who are against how people look, this is the church for you! Wow wow wow!

name: Cornelia Farm
text:
If you are looking for a church to make you feel warm & fuzzy without knowing and applying the Word, look elsewhere. 12th Street Baptist is a family of believers who are striving together to hold ourselves accountable to God and his Word and to live out our faith in our day-to-day lives. This means taking hard looks at our opinions and biases and taking everything back to Scripture, where there are many uncomfortable yet necessary truths. We are always found wanting when we compare ourselves to God’s standard, but the Good News is that the grace of Jesus covers us as we are sanctified every day in our relationship with Him.

We are an intentional church. Here, we get into theology; we ask hard questions; we dive into the nitty-gritty details of life and we apply what we’ve learned about God to our daily lives and relationships. Is it hard? Yes. Is it sometimes uncomfortable? Absolutely. But the point of our faith is not to be comfortable. It is to know the Truth and to lovingly live it out with the help and grace of Jesus Christ. And it is WORTH IT.

If that’s not what you want, all the best to you in your search. But if you want a family of fellow sinners saved by grace who are all struggling together, held together by our faith and taking everything back to the Cross, then this may be the family for you.

text:
I grew up as a Southern Baptist, and over the past 40 years as a Christ follower, and as someone who has been to many, many, many, churches, (Baptist, Church of Christ, and Presbyterian) across the United States and visiting churches across the world as a US Marine. All I can say is this, having lived in the South in the USA, and also traveling across the world as a Marine. Having listened to the best Baptist Pastors in the USA, I have never heard a  better pastor or speaker of the “Word” than the current pastor of Mount Joy Baptist church in Jasper AL. If you want a Bible-based ministry, with honest people, and honest biblical teachings, then you WILL NOT FIND A BETTER  church than Mount Joy Baptist Church!

This is coming from someone who has been a doubter and believer in the WORD.

This Church and this Pastor have restored my faith in GOD, and the truth of God’s Word!!

Plus, I really love the architecture of this Church. It is simple, but incredibly well laid out and has very good materials. Whoever built this Church was a person of detail.

text:
My 2 year old attends daycare here and it is phenomenal! Everyone is friendly, patient, and know how to handle kids. My daughter gets so excited every time we pull up in the parking lot. Classrooms are huge for all ages and there's also an art room, a playground, a gymnasium, a large formal hall with stage, and a chapel. The church services and study classes are also great. Nobody is judgemental and I do not get that fake super happy churchy vibe from anyone like I have at just about every other one I've been to.
There's a good mix of kids, teens, young adults, middle age, and seniors. I highly recommend.

name: Brad Tucker
text:
I have been a Christian all my life but continued to live in sin. I always wanted to be free from sin but believed I could live in sin & still go to heaven. After going to Fire & Grace & reading Pastor Deans book grace abuse I realized I needed to repent & fully commit to God. Pastor Dean gave me his personal cell phone # & has always been there for me & has answered every question I have ever had. He taught me how to get free from demons. I didn’t realize the reason I wasn’t able to stop sinning was because of demons. Once I rebuked them & got them out of my life I was able to be free. I will not let them back in my life! I have confidence now that I am living a life pleasing to God & I know that one day I will receive the crown of Life. God used Pastor Dean to reach me & disciple me. I am now a servant of Christ. It is a wonderful thing to live without anything separating you from God!
God bless Pastor Dean & Nancy

name: Deb Ridings
text:
Dean Odle has opened my eyes to many things in his teachings that I had previously been taught wrong...as in, not lining up with the Word, and now it does...and it was right there in the Bible all along, I just never saw it or understood it.  Some of the comments here are not in Christian love, they are out right attacks.  Maybe these people should come under authority of a pastor somewhere else....and the pastor IS the authority of his flock.  The things that Dean brings out of the scriptures are not open to interpretation by man, the Holy Spirit gives the understanding.  He does expound on principles and such, but that is a normal way of getting thoughts across.  And I think he does a fabulous job of bringing out points that I had previously over looked.  It is for those who have eyes to see and ears to hear, regardless who is teaching it.  Dean knows what he knows and seems to be willing to share it with a cheerful heart.  My family enjoys his teachings online, we are too far to go to worship in person, but hope to some day soon!
~Deb in Cleveland, GA

name: Plasso Platoos
text: I don't know that I have ever felt so at home in any church as I did at this one. Real worship....in Spirit and Truth. The Word of The Lord is filling this place.

name: Dustin Wells
text:
Dean Odle, the pastor of this church shows all the classic signs of a cult leader. He refuses to hear any opinion on the Bible that differs from his own personal interpretation. If someone dares to share scripture on his social media that contradicts his chosen interpretation of the Bible he will delete their comments and block them, thereby controlling what information his "flock" gets to read.

He boasts of himself saying things like "I have 31 years of fruit leading people to repentance and faith in blood of Jesus Christ and His resurrection from the dead. I have seen lives changed as they made Jesus Lord of their lives. I seen the cripple work, the deaf hear, the dying cancer patient healed and even the dead raised in Jesus name. I have demons out of witches, Satanists and many others in Jesus name to see them go on to serve God in the truth of the New Covenant."

As a preacher who tells people they don't have to be obedient to what God said, this above statement of his qualifies him to fit these words spoken by Jesus himself, “Not everyone who says to Me, ‘Lord, Lord,’ shall enter the kingdom of heaven, but he who does the will of My Father in heaven.  Many will say to Me in that day, ‘Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in Your name, cast out demons in Your name, and done many wonders in Your name?’  And then I will declare to them, ‘I never knew you; depart from Me, you who practice lawlessness!’
Matthew 7:21‭-‬23 NKJV

This man is a false prophet by the standards of Deuteronomy 13, and he is leading people to their own destruction. STAY AWAY!

name: Sandra Mahoney
text: This is where you heard truth and the whole word of God !  Anointed pastor !

name: Jodi S
text:
The pastor of this church is the most shameful disgrace to the name of Christ that I've ever witnessed. He is argumentative, arrogant, unkind, unloving, impatient, quick to anger, hateful, narcissistic, manipulative, controlling, deceiving, boastful and self righteous. His ministry revolves around arguing with everyone and blocking anyone who disagrees with him. His attitude is disgusting and his demeanor is one in which he thinks he's better/smarter/more righteous than everyone else.

He runs his church with complete authority to himself, like a cult. I've never seen a better example of a false teacher.

Don't be deceived by his YouTube and Facebook popularity, his internet followers have never met him and don't really know what goes on in his church, behind the scenes. Beware of men like this, who talk up themselves constantly and boast of all the great things they've done. Where there is no humility, there is no repentance and where there's no repentance, there is no Christ.

name: Paul L
text:
I come from the once Christian, now atheist and secular nation called Sweden. As most people can imagine, finding a church where the whole Bible is preached is quite rare to come by in this country. I chose to visit Fire and Grace Church after being born again in 2015, having read the Bible for myself, and watched more or less all of FGC sermons. Furthermore, I listened to a vast array of other sermons by other preachers, pastors and church leaders. Both mainstream and more ”controversial”. Even many youtubers.

While visiting FGC I have felt nothing but sincere hospitality, charity and Spirit-led fellowship. I hope to visit them from time to time. Not because I am obligated to do so, but because I want to.

I prefer face-to-face interactions when it comes to spiritual matters in order to make my own spiritual opinion on topics like these, rather than relying too much on online opinion forgers.

Philippians 2:12

God Bless, Paul Lögdberg

name: Marissa Wiles
text:
While I have not attended this church/center, I can tell you what it is like being their neighbors. They play their music so loudly they wake up toddlers in the neighborhood across the street. The bass is so loud you can hear it over your tv, and if you work from home you should pray you don't take phone calls.

When I asked them to turn it down I was told they would "see what they could do" but that there was "no city ordinance that can make us turn it down" the man had "checked and my wife is a lawyer". If this is the attitude you put off from your outreach, I doubt people want part of it. After waking my 2 year old up two days in a row from bedtime and his nap, you should have a little compassion for people.

Instead of calling the police, I chose to ask nicely. But as I was leaving, an officer was already pulling up to tell them to turn it down. Guess someone was tired of asking nicely.

name: Jessica Wolfe
text: I’ve attended many different churches during my 50 years of life. The first time I attended at Heritage it was still in back of the cabinet shop. I had already asked Jesus to come into my heart years before but, the night before attending Heritage I was watching a late, late church service on T.V.  at the end of the service they did The Sinners Prayer and I repeated it wanting to renew my relationship with Our Father ! A message came to me so clearly afterwards telling me to find a Home Church and worship with fellow Christians again! I told my husband that I was going to Church in the morning, he shocked me by asking if he could go to! I told him of course he could! He was the one who suggested Heritage because our friend Charlie went there, I was just going to go to Garywood. As soon as we walked into Heritage I felt like I had come home!!! The people were so friendly and filled with The Spirit of The Lord . The music is one of my favorite parts! But Brother Mark’s sermon blew me away, I was really home. After a couple of years we moved to Gulf Shores, but Heritage still remained in my heart! I was one of the first to be baptized in the new church that my husband and several of our friends helped build! I’m back now and will be returning home very soon! Also, anyone who has never had a relationship with God? This is the church for you! They are wonderful with new born again Christians! Everyone is treated as family, no matter what your story is, and many churches could learn from their example!
